  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F.",
    "Mix sesame seed paste, almond butter, coconut oil, maple syrup, vanilla extract, baking soda, and salt in a bowl until smooth.",
    "Stir in optional sesame seeds for added texture.",
    "Press the mixture into an 8x8 inch dish lined with parchment paper for easy removal.",
    "Bake for 15 minutes or until firm to touch. Let cool before serving.",
    "For garnish, drizzle with a bit of maple syrup and sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds."
